Sheep pox and goat pox, Russia
------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 18 Oct 2013 from Dr Evgeny Nepoklonov, Deputy Head, Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance, Ministry of Agriculture, Moscow, Russia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 3 Sep 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 9 Sep 2013
Report date: 18 Oct 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 18 Oct 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 25 Apr 2013
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Capripoxvirus_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Bura village, Kalgansky, [Zabaykalsky territory]
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Sep 2013
Outbreak status: resolved (11 Oct 2013)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 269 / 55 /0 / 55 /0
Outbreak statistics
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 20.45 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent / 24.45 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: the outbreak was located 3 kilometers [2 mi] away from the Chinese border.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); disinfection of premises/establishment(s); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Government budget institution "Zabaykalsky territory veterinary laboratory" (local laboratory) / sheep / optical microscopy / 9 Sep 2013/ Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

